<div class="help-container">
  <h1>SSH on Mac</h1>
  <div class="install-git-on-mac">
    There are a lot of different ways to install git on OS X. The recommended way is either with <a href="http://mxcl.github.com/homebrew/">Homebrew</a> or <a href="http://www.macports.org/">MacPorts</a>.
  </div>
  <div class="generate-mac-ssh-key">
    <h2>Create SSH Key</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>open Terminal</li>
      <li>mkdir ~/.ssh</li>
      <li>cd ~/.ssh</li>
      <li>ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "name@email.com"</li>
      <li>Enter a passphrase (remember it)</li>
      <li>Your key should be generated</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
  <div class="get-ssh-key">
    <h2>Get Your SSH Key</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Open Terminal</li>
      <li>cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub | pbcopy</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
  <div class="add-ssh-key-to-account">
    <h2>Add SSH Key to Account</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Visit <%= link_to "add ssh key", "/account/ssh" %> in your <%= link_to "account settings", "/account" %></li>
      <li>Click Add Key</li>
      <li>Give the key a name</li>
      <li>Paste the key you copied into the key text field</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>
